BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali has said 
the results of His Majesty King Husayn's visit to the United 
States shifted the Jordanian-U.S. relations to a very advanced 
stage compared with how they were in the past. 
  In an exclusive statement to the Jordanian News Agency, Dr. 
al-Majali said relations between the two friendly countries will 
witness substantial progress in various fields, especially since 
His Majesty King Husayn's visit has laid down strong bases for 
bolstering and developing these relations, which became clearer 
concerning the peace process. 
  He said His Majesty King Husayn's talks with U.S. President 
Bill Clinton dotted the i's concerning the economic issue and 
peace. 
  He emphasized that the U.S. President was clear when he 
stressed that Jordan should not bear alone the responsibility of 
peace, but all countries should share Jordan in shouldering this 
responsibility. 

